Variation.
In a 
14.5 mm
HL specimen (NSMT-P 92270; 
Fig. 204
), dark spots are serially arranged along the dorsal contour of the trunk and tail. These spots are prominent only when young, and are not found in larger specimens (
Figs. 202–203
).

Distribution. Restricted to Japan and Taiwan . Known from off the Pacific coasts of Japan northward to Iwaki ( Fukushima Pref. , 37.00ºN ), Okinawa Trough, and northern South China Sea, at depths of 350‾ 755 m (Okamura 1982;
Chiou et al. 2004a
;
Shao et al. 2008a
, 2008b ; this study; Appendix 3-12E). Uncommon.
